Packages that use FeatureSet
com.github.seqware.queryengine.backInterfaces Provides interfaces that are only of interest to users working on the back-end 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.factory Provides the classes that the RESTful interface will use to construct interfaces that use the back-end without reference to the specific back-end. 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.impl Provides the classes that implement the actual back-end for various database (or lack of database) types 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.impl.protobufIO This package contains the classes that specifically handle protobuffer serialization to and from the back-end. 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.model Provides the classes that the RESTful API will interact with. 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.model.impl.hbasemrlazy Provides classes that 'lazily' allow their members to persist their own membership and use Map/Reduce to determine attributes about themselves. 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.model.impl.inMemory Provides classes that support a simple in-memory implementation of the various model classes. 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.model.impl.lazy Provides classes that 'lazily' allow their members to persist their own membership. 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.plugins Provides the interfaces that an external plugin developer would need to conform to in order for the Query Engine to install and run properly. 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.plugins.hbasemr Provides classes that support and implement hbase implementations of plug-ins. 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.plugins.inmemory Provides classes that support and implement in-memory mock-ups for plugins. 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.plugins.plugins Provides plug-in implementations 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.system.exporters Command-line tools for exporting files to external file types. 
com.github.seqware.queryengine.util Provides utility classes for accessing this API via the model
